<br>
&gt;Looking For Groups<br>
&gt;Auctions<br>
&gt;Personal Conversations<br>
<br>
Sorry, but I appreciate the relative silence of the zones without all of that irelevant chit chat that happens on other servers.  Yes I know I can turn it off, but I keep it on case of that ever dominate &quot;Train to Zone&quot; or &quot;Xzep cf Dser&quot; if I dont understand it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Before it gets out of hand, Here is a guide on how things work.<br>
<br>
&gt; LOOKING FOR GROUP <br>
Turn on LFG flag by typing /lfg on <br>
Those that are looking for people to join their group do a &quot;/who lfg&quot;  That tells you who in zone is looking for a group.<br>
Then you send them a TELL (not a shout) asking them to join your group. Easy<br>
<br>
&gt; AUCTIONS<br>
While I wish it was a bit easier to do, ie, a specific zone like East Commons to set up shop in, It is restricted to City Zones ONLY!  It will be fun to visit various cities, trying to learn the languages, to find someone selling a Fungi Tunic.  That was the way Verant made it and that is the way we need to do it<br>
<br>
&gt;PERSONAL CONVERSATIONS<br>
Jeesh - Plain and Simple - TAKE IT TO TELLS!  I went in to GFay yesterday and with 190 people, it was horrible.  I, and others do not need to hear what movie you saw the other night or how drunk you were or a conversation between two friends.<br>
<br>
Ok, I am not tryng to &quot;preach&quot; what you should do, but if you are on this server to truly RP, you wont abuse the shout channel.  I just had to get this of my chest before it gets worse.<br>
